        <span class="card-title white-text"><%= link_to 'Details', pages_path(page: 'hackathon', anchor: 'details')%></span>
      </div>
      <div class="card green lighten-1 col s6">
        <span class="card-title white-text"><%= link_to 'Hosts', pages_path(page: 'hackathon', anchor: 'hosts')%></span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <a id="details"></a>
  <div class="section no-pad-bot red lighten-1 ">
    <div class="container padding row">
      <div class="col s6">
        <span class="card-title white-text agenda-content" style="font-size: 200%">Agenda</span>
        <p class="flow-text white-text agenda-content">10:00 a.m. - 10:30- a.m. Check In</p>
        <p class="flow-text white-text agenda-content">10:30 a.m. - 11:00 a.m. Speaker</p>
        <p class="flow-text white-text agenda-content">12:30 p.m. - Lunch</p>
        <p class="flow-text white-text agenda-content">11:00 a.m. - 3:30 p.m. Hack!</p>
        <p class="flow-text white-text agenda-content">3:00 p.m. - 3:30 p.m. Judging</p>
        <p class="flow-text white-text agenda-content">3:30 p.m. - 3:50 p.m. Walk Around</p>
        <p class="flow-text white-text agenda-content">3:50 p.m. - 4:00 p.m. Prizes and Closing Speech</p>
        <p class="flow-text white-text agenda-content">3:30 p.m. - 4:00 p.m.   Closing Panel</p>
        <p class="flow-text white-text agenda-content" style="font-size: 140%">
          Food and drink will be provided! Please remember to note any allergies or other dietary
          restrictions on the registration form.
      </div>
      <div class="col s6">
        <span class="card-title white-text agenda-content" style="font-size: 200%">More Information</span>
        <p class = "white-text flow-text" style="font-size: 130%">
          BearHacks, hosted by Berkeley’s chapters of Eta Kappa Nu and Upsilon Pi Epsilon,  
          is an educational hackathon geared towards high school students, especially those
          with little to no coding experience. In a 6-hour period, students will have the
          opportunity to work on a small-scale project of their own choosing with teammates
          or by themselves, and current Berkeley Computer Science undergraduates will be
          there to offer individualized guidance. There will also be numerous booths set up
          in the venue, where students can learn the fundamentals of valuable skills such as
          JavaScript, CSS, iOS development, website development, and more, and incorporate them
          into their own projects! BearHacks 2016 is the inaugural event for this program, and
          we’re excited to have you come out and learn with us! 
        </p>
        <p class = "white-text flow-text" style="font-size: 150%">
          Questions?: Email serv@hkn.eecs.berkeley.edu
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
